A '''mental maze''' was a toy used to help [[Jedi training/Legends|train]] [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Youngling/Legends|younglings]] in the use and [[Force power/Legends|manipulation]] of [[The Force/Legends|the Force]]. They were metal spheres of varying sizes which a person would project part of their self into. The smaller the sphere, the more complicated it would be to get out of; however, once a youngling got the hang of using the mazes, it could be easy. In [[12 ABY/Legends|12 ABY]], using [[Alter Mind]] and the maze's natural properties, [[Irek Ismaren]] tried to trap [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] in the smallest and most complex sphere from [[Plett]]'s collection of Jedi training tools. The maze was composed of many layers of concentric spheres, linked by apertures which Organa Solo experienced as one-way gates. She also experienced frightening visions inside, though they may have originated from Ismaren or from her own subconscious.

